text: Yoronjima (与論島, Okinawan and Yoron: ユンヌ Yunnu; Kunigami: ユンヌー Yunnuu) is one of the Amami Islands of Okinawa Prefecture, Japan. In 2018, it had 5,056 people. Most of them are Ryukyuan, who are the natives of the Ryūkyū Islands. ==Related pages== * Amami Islands == References == Category:Ryukyu Islands
title: Yoronjima
